* Model

** Model Diagram


file:ModelDiagram.png

** Model Compartments 
| Compartment | Definitions                       |
| $S$         | Susceptible individuals           |
| $L$         | Latently infected individuals     |
| $I$         | Infectious individuals            |
| $R_t$       | Treated individuals               |
| $R$         | Completely recovered individuals  |
** Model Parameters
Here is model parameter definitions and their corresponding values that we are using
from literature. We estimate three parameters: transmission risk
$\beta$, complete recovery rate $\eta$ and relapse rate $\sigma$. We
also estimated three initial conditions $S(0)$, $L(0)$ and $R_{t}(0)$.

| Parameters | Definitions                                                              |   Values | Reference |
| $\Delta$   | Recruitment rate in the population                                       |   0.0008 |           |
| $\mu$      | Per capita mortality rate                                                | 0.000043 |           |
| $\alpha$   | Per capita rate related to asymptomatic period in general population     |  0.00975 |           |
| $p$        | Proportion of symptomatic individuals                                    |   0.9967 |           |
| $\gamma$   | Per capita recovery rate of symptoatic individuals in general population |   0.0087 |           |
| $\delta$   | Per capita disease mortality rate of symptomatic individuals             |   0.0067 |           |
| $N(0)$     | Initial total population                                                 | 99000000 | Data      |
| $I(0)$     | Initial infected population                                              |      388 | Data      |
| $D(0)$     | Disease induced death compartment                                        |        2 | Data      |




* Fitting

I fitted the parameters transmission risk $\beta$, complete recovery
rate $\nu$ and relapse rate $\sigma$ as well as three initial
conditions using 'fminsearchbnd' in Matlab.  For rest of the
parameters and initial conditions, I either use estimates from
literature or use an assumed value [[Model Parameters][See Here]].

I ran the estimation routine starting from $32$ random initial guesses for
the parameters between their lower and upper bound. I finally save the
parameter estimates that maximizes the likelihood most as best
parameter estimates. 

** Parameter Estimates
*Model Parameters*
| Parameters | Definition                        | Bounds   | Estimate     | Range |
| $\beta$    | Transmission risk ($y^{-1}$)      | [0, 10]  | $0.2369$     | [0.1553,1.6598] |
| $\sigma$   | Relapse rate ($y^{-1}$)           | [0.5, 8] | $0.5528$     | [0.5000,6.9530] |
| $\eta$     | Complete recovery rate ($y^{-1}$) | [0.2, 6] | $0.3011$     | [0.2000,5.9968] |

*Initial Conditions*

| Initial State | Definition                               | Estimate  | Range |
| $S(0)$        | Initial susceptible population           |  98854000 | [96063000,98957000] |
| $L(0)$        | Initial latent population                |    113360 | [35864,191400] |
| $R_{t}(0)$    | Initial temporarily recovered population |       1029 |    [0,1200]    |


$R(0)$ was calculated as $N(0)-S(0)-L(0)-I(0)-D(0)-R_t(0)$.

